## Common Development Tasks

### Starting a New Template

```
1. Create this CLAUDE.md from the template
2. Update {{placeholders}} with project-specific values
3. Create templateDetails.xml with positions and parameters
4. Create joomla.asset.json for asset registration
5. Create index.php entry point
6. Set up SCSS partials (if using SCSS)
7. Discover and activate in Joomla admin
```

### Adding a Template Override

```
1. Identify the original file in components/com_*/tmpl/ or modules/mod_*/tmpl/
2. Copy to templates/{{TEMPLATE_NAME}}/html/com_*/view/file.php
3. Modify the copy — Joomla loads overrides automatically
4. Test across all relevant content items
```

### Adding a Module Position

```
1. Add <position> to templateDetails.xml
2. Add <jdoc:include type="modules" name="position-name" /> to index.php
3. Wrap in conditional: <?php if ($this->countModules('position-name')): ?>
```

### Setting Up SCSS Build

```
1. Create scss/ directory with partials
2. Configure build tool (Vite/Webpack/sass CLI)
3. Output compiled CSS to css/template.css
4. Add watch command for development
```

### Creating a Child Template

```
1. Create new directory: templates/{{TEMPLATE_NAME}}_child/
2. Inherit from parent in templateDetails.xml: <inheritable>1</inheritable>
3. Override only the files you need to change
4. Child template overrides take precedence over parent
```

### Debugging Template Issues

```
1. Enable Joomla debug mode: Global Configuration > System > Debug
2. Check template position assignments: Extensions > Modules
3. Preview module positions: ?tp=1 URL parameter
4. Check browser dev tools for CSS specificity conflicts
5. Check Joomla error log: E:\www\{{DOMAIN}}/error.log
```

